# Solaar reads this file as ~/.config/solaar/rules.yaml.
# It contains zero or more YAML documents; each document is one Solaar rule.
#
# Rules trigger from HID++ notifications, so buttons must first be set to a
# diverted action in Solaar's Key/Button Diversion setting. Under Wayland,
# actions that synthesize input use /dev/uinput; the system Logitech module
# installs Solaar's udev rules through hardware.logitech.wireless.enable.
#
# === Thumb-button mouse gestures (MX Master 4 + MX Master 3S) ===
#
# Both mice drive the SAME directional gesture scheme from their thumb button.
# On the MX Master 4 that thumb button is `Haptic` (control 416); on the
# MX Master 3S it is `Mouse Gesture Button` (control 195). The two buttons sit
# in the same physical thumb position, so they intentionally share one rule
# set and behave identically.
#
# Each button is set to "Mouse Gestures" divert mode (divert-keys = 2) by
# scripts/linux/config-solaar.sh. In that mode the button reports the
# MOUSE_GESTURE feature with directional data while held, instead of a plain
# key press. The rules below key on the `MouseGesture` condition (a feature
# match), NOT a key label, so one rule set fires for whichever mouse sent the
# gesture. No `Device:` guard is needed or wanted here: the goal is for both
# thumb buttons to act the same. (The MX Master 4 ALSO exposes its own
# `Mouse Gesture Button` at control 195, but it is left Regular — firmware
# handled, never reaches the rule engine — so it cannot collide with these.)
#
# === Per-desktop actions, selected at chezmoi apply time ===
#
# The gesture ACTIONS are desktop-specific D-Bus calls, so this template
# renders one of two variants via lookPath: a KDE host (plasmashell on PATH —
# Fedora KDE Spin, Ubuntu Studio) gets KWin global-shortcut actions; a
# GNOME-only host (gnome-shell without plasmashell — Fedora Workstation,
# Ubuntu Desktop) gets GNOME Shell D-Bus actions. When NEITHER desktop is on
# PATH (headless host, container, CI render) the KDE variant is rendered —
# inert without a desktop, and it keeps CI artifacts deterministic. The haptic
# confirm path is desktop-agnostic and identical in both variants.
#
# KDE map. Verified host: Plasma 6.6.5 Wayland; qdbus-qt6 at
# /usr/bin/qdbus-qt6; KWin shortcuts "Grid View", "Show Desktop",
# "Window Quick Tile Left", "Window Quick Tile Right" all present
# (qdbus-qt6 org.kde.kglobalaccel /component/kwin shortcutNames); krunner
# method org.kde.krunner.App.toggleDisplay present (qdbus-qt6 org.kde.krunner
# /App). Solaar 1.1.19.
#
#   hold + flick Up    -> Desktop Grid         (Grid View)        + haptic
#   hold + flick Down  -> Show Desktop / peek   (Show Desktop)     + haptic
#   hold + flick Left  -> snap window left      (Window Quick Tile Left)  + haptic
#   hold + flick Right -> snap window right     (Window Quick Tile Right) + haptic
#   press, no movement -> KRunner launcher      (krunner toggleDisplay)
#
# GNOME map (Fedora Workstation / Ubuntu Desktop). Only GNOME Shell's STABLE
# D-Bus surface is used — the org.gnome.Shell OverviewActive property and
# FocusSearch method (js/ui/shellDBus.js); org.gnome.Shell.Eval is disabled
# outside unsafe mode and is deliberately not used:
#
#   hold + flick Up    -> Activities overview   (OverviewActive=true)   + haptic
#   hold + flick Down  -> leave the overview    (OverviewActive=false)  + haptic
#   hold + flick Left  -> haptic tick only (see below)
#   hold + flick Right -> haptic tick only (see below)
#   press, no movement -> overview search       (FocusSearch — the KRunner analog)
#
# GNOME exposes no stable D-Bus method for window tiling or workspace
# switching (the KDE Left/Right actions), and simulating GNOME's default
# <Super>Left / <Super>Right keybindings via Solaar's KeyPress would need
# /dev/uinput write access that stock hosts don't grant. Left/Right therefore
# keep only the haptic confirm — the flick still registers tactilely — until a
# stable action exists to wire here. gdbus ships with GLib on every GNOME host.
#
# Haptic confirm: each of the four DIRECTIONAL gestures also fires
# `mxm4-haptic "SUBTLE COLLISION"` — a tactile "your flick registered" tick,
# Logi-action-ring style. It uses the mxm4-hapticd daemon client, invoked by
# its ABSOLUTE path ~/.local/bin/mxm4-haptic (the autostart Solaar systemd
# user service has NO guaranteed ~/.local/bin on PATH, so a bare `mxm4-haptic`
# would not resolve — the rendered Execute below carries the full path), NOT
# `Set: [null, haptic-play, ...]`: the daemon does a direct hidraw write with
# no HID++ ack wait, so the pulse is instant and consistent (see the root
# AGENTS.md "Solaar haptic playback" alternatives table). The press-with-no-
# movement launcher rule is intentionally left silent — KRunner / the GNOME
# overview visibly pops up, so it is self-confirming and needs no tick. The
# Execute list form runs through subprocess.Popen with shell=False (no
# quoting/injection surface).
#
# Wayland caveat (printed by `solaar show`): "rules cannot access modifier
# keys in Wayland". Every action below uses a DBus Execute instead of a
# KeyPress so it never depends on modifier state; invokeShortcut on the
# org.kde.kglobalaccel /component/kwin interface bypasses keymap/layout. The
# Grid View and Overview effects must stay enabled in System Settings ->
# Desktop Effects; if disabled, invokeShortcut silently no-ops (re-enable the
# effect rather than adding a per-press loadEffect call).
#
# Diversion setup is owned by scripts/linux/config-solaar.sh (TARGETS array):
#   B04200000000 divert-keys.416 = 2  (MX Master 4 Haptic -> Mouse Gestures)
#   B03400000000 divert-keys.195 = 2  (MX Master 3S Gesture Button -> Mouse Gestures)
# Do NOT divert via `solaar config ... divert-keys` on 1.1.19 (it flips the
# runtime state but crashes during persistence); config-solaar.sh edits
# config.yaml directly and restarts Solaar only when something changed.
{{- $gnomeRules := and (lookPath "gnome-shell") (not (lookPath "plasmashell")) }}
---
- MouseGesture: Mouse Up
{{ if $gnomeRules -}}
- Execute: [gdbus, call, --session, --dest, org.gnome.Shell, --object-path, /org/gnome/Shell, --method, org.freedesktop.DBus.Properties.Set, org.gnome.Shell, OverviewActive, "<true>"]
{{ else -}}
- Execute: [qdbus-qt6, org.kde.kglobalaccel, /component/kwin, invokeShortcut, Grid View]
{{ end -}}
- Execute: ["{{ .chezmoi.homeDir }}/.local/bin/mxm4-haptic", "SUBTLE COLLISION"]
...

---
- MouseGesture: Mouse Down
{{ if $gnomeRules -}}
- Execute: [gdbus, call, --session, --dest, org.gnome.Shell, --object-path, /org/gnome/Shell, --method, org.freedesktop.DBus.Properties.Set, org.gnome.Shell, OverviewActive, "<false>"]
{{ else -}}
- Execute: [qdbus-qt6, org.kde.kglobalaccel, /component/kwin, invokeShortcut, Show Desktop]
{{ end -}}
- Execute: ["{{ .chezmoi.homeDir }}/.local/bin/mxm4-haptic", "SUBTLE COLLISION"]
...

---
- MouseGesture: Mouse Left
{{ if not $gnomeRules -}}
- Execute: [qdbus-qt6, org.kde.kglobalaccel, /component/kwin, invokeShortcut, Window Quick Tile Left]
{{ end -}}
- Execute: ["{{ .chezmoi.homeDir }}/.local/bin/mxm4-haptic", "SUBTLE COLLISION"]
...

---
- MouseGesture: Mouse Right
{{ if not $gnomeRules -}}
- Execute: [qdbus-qt6, org.kde.kglobalaccel, /component/kwin, invokeShortcut, Window Quick Tile Right]
{{ end -}}
- Execute: ["{{ .chezmoi.homeDir }}/.local/bin/mxm4-haptic", "SUBTLE COLLISION"]
...

# Press with no movement (a plain click on the gesture-diverted thumb button)
# reports a zero-movement MOUSE_GESTURE, matched by an empty MouseGesture list.
# It cannot collide with the directional rules above: each gesture notification
# matches exactly one of these five documents (the movement count differs).
---
- MouseGesture: []
{{ if $gnomeRules -}}
- Execute: [gdbus, call, --session, --dest, org.gnome.Shell, --object-path, /org/gnome/Shell, --method, org.gnome.Shell.FocusSearch]
{{ else -}}
- Execute: [qdbus-qt6, org.kde.krunner, /App, org.kde.krunner.App.toggleDisplay]
{{ end -}}
...

# Example: map a diverted Back Button press to Alt+Left.
# ---
# - Key: [Back Button, pressed]
# - KeyPress: [Alt_L, Left, click]
# ...
#
# Example: use thumb-wheel notifications for horizontal scrolling.
# Requires THUMB WHEEL diversion enabled in Solaar.
# ---
# - Feature: THUMB WHEEL
# - Rule: [Test: thumb_wheel_up, MouseScroll: [-1, 0]]
# - Rule: [Test: thumb_wheel_down, MouseScroll: [1, 0]]
# ...
